docs.abstract: A pilot program will pick up goods and move them to Amazon warehouses. It could expand over time into more of a threat to established delivery companies.
docs.snippet: A pilot program will pick up goods and move them to Amazon warehouses. It could expand over time into more of a threat to established delivery companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Amazon is planning to test a program this year that would replace some delivery services now done by United Parcel Service and FedEx.

headline.main: Amazon to Test a New Delivery Service for Sellers
headline.print_headline: Amazon to Test Delivery Service That May Compete With UPS and FedEx

docs.abstract: The push by two investment funds to have Apple give parents better controls over their children’s iPhones shows Silicon Valley has lost its exalted status.
docs.snippet: The push by two investment funds to have Apple give parents better controls over their children’s iPhones shows Silicon Valley has lost its exalted status.
docs.lead_paragraph: The tech backlash has caught up to Apple. The activist hedge fund Jana Partners and the California State Teachers’ Retirement System want Apple to give parents better controls over their children’s iPhones. It’s an unusual issue for an activist, and apps from Facebook and Snap would make better targets.

headline.main: Tech Backlash Catches Up to Apple

docs.abstract: Photographs taken on the plane, whose engine exploded, show panicked passengers with the masks around their mouths but not their noses.
docs.snippet: Photographs taken on the plane, whose engine exploded, show panicked passengers with the masks around their mouths but not their noses.
docs.lead_paragraph: On the list of possible midair emergencies, airline passengers are instructed on every flight what to do if the cabin pressure suddenly drops. “If the airplane loses pressure, oxygen masks will drop automatically,” the safety video on American Airlines flights says. “The yellow cup goes around your mouth and nose.”

headline.main: On Southwest 1380, Confusion and Distraction as Oxygen Masks Dropped

byline.original: By Matthew Haag and Maya Salam

docs.abstract: Natalie Massenet, the fashion entrepreneur, has teamed up with the investor Nick Brown to invest in e-commerce start-ups.
docs.snippet: Natalie Massenet, the fashion entrepreneur, has teamed up with the investor Nick Brown to invest in e-commerce start-ups.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Natalie Massenet said she had planned to keep a low profile after she stepped down in 2015 as the executive chairwoman of Net-a-Porter, the popular luxury e-commerce site she founded.

headline.main: Net-a-Porter Founder’s Next Act Is a Venture Capital Firm
headline.print_headline: Net-a-Porter Founder Gets A Second Act

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced

docs.abstract: Leading Silicon Valley entrepreneurs are forming a Founders for Change coalition to deliver a message to the white- and male-dominated world of venture capital.
docs.snippet: Leading Silicon Valley entrepreneurs are forming a Founders for Change coalition to deliver a message to the white- and male-dominated world of venture capital.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — When Trevor McFedries set out last year to raise money for Brud, his robotics and artificial intelligence start-up, he found himself in many meetings with “a ton of white guy” venture capitalists.

headline.main: Hundreds of Start-Ups Tell Investors: Diversify, or Keep Your Money
headline.print_headline: Note to Venture Capitalists:  Diversify, or Keep Your Millions

docs.abstract: The changes the social network recently made to its news feed has some advertisers thinking there will be opportunities for growth in video.
docs.snippet: The changes the social network recently made to its news feed has some advertisers thinking there will be opportunities for growth in video.
docs.lead_paragraph: Facebook made waves in the media industry with its recent announcement that it would put a new focus on “meaningful social interactions” with close friends and family in its News Feed — the column that people scroll through when they open the site — instead of content from publishers and brands.

headline.main: As Facebook Changes Its Feed, Advertisers See Video Ambitions

docs.abstract: Elaine Wynn, the casino and resort company’s largest shareholder and Mr. Wynn’s ex-wife, is fighting to oust a longtime board member who is close to Mr. Wynn.
docs.snippet: Elaine Wynn, the casino and resort company’s largest shareholder and Mr. Wynn’s ex-wife, is fighting to oust a longtime board member who is close to Mr. Wynn.
docs.lead_paragraph: Elaine Wynn, known as the Queen of Las Vegas for her long involvement with Mirage and Wynn Resorts, the casino and resort companies she founded with her ex-husband Steve Wynn, might seem an unlikely champion of shareholder rights and good corporate governance.

headline.main: With Steve Wynn Gone, ‘Queen of Las Vegas’ Does Boardroom Battle
headline.print_headline: The Other Wynn Holds a Stake. And Has a Say.

docs.abstract: Swiss prosecutors opened an investigation days after the French luxury group denied allegations that it had used a Swiss-based scheme to evade taxes.
docs.snippet: Swiss prosecutors opened an investigation days after the French luxury group denied allegations that it had used a Swiss-based scheme to evade taxes.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Swiss prosecutors said on Wednesday they had opened a criminal investigation into a tax case involving the French luxury group Kering, widening the legal scrutiny of its tax practices in Europe.

headline.main: Kering, Owner of Gucci and Saint Laurent, Faces Swiss Tax Inquiry

docs.abstract: As part of the filing, the studio said it released anyone “who suffered or witnessed any form of sexual misconduct by Harvey Weinstein” from nondisclosure agreements.
docs.snippet: As part of the filing, the studio said it released anyone “who suffered or witnessed any form of sexual misconduct by Harvey Weinstein” from nondisclosure agreements.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The Weinstein Company clung to life longer than anyone in Hollywood expected following a sexual harassment scandal so big that it started a global workplace reckoning.

headline.main: Weinstein Company Files for Bankruptcy and Revokes Nondisclosure Agreements
headline.print_headline: Weinstein Company Files for Bankruptcy Protection

docs.abstract: A National Limousine Association campaign featuring Pamela Anderson encourages ride-sharing customers to watch out for their safety, but critics say it is only trying to make competitors look bad.
docs.snippet: A National Limousine Association campaign featuring Pamela Anderson encourages ride-sharing customers to watch out for their safety, but critics say it is only trying to make competitors look bad.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pamela Anderson walks down a city street and uses her cellphone to book a ride. Along the way, she passes a newspaper and street signs that say, “Hollywood Sexual Harassment Scandal Reaches New Lows” and “U.S. Senator Accused of Groping.” When she gets into the car, she sees another sign that says, “Ride-Hail Drivers Suspected of Rape.” The car doors lock, and the driver turns around and suggestively asks, “Shall we?” Just then, “#MeToo” pops up on her phone’s screen.

headline.main: Ad Warns Riders About Uber and Lyft, but Some Call It Alarmist
